    public class PlaceCell
extends javax.swing.JButton
    Represents a Place in the city on the Swing interface. It is a button, which name is the place name. A PlaceCell needs to store a reference to the place that it represents. However, this place should not be modified by the PlaceCell When the user clicks on a PlaceCell the CityPanel will show the place description if the Place was previously visited.

    Abel Serrano Juste
